    t1_title: 'Calculate left-to-right, not right-to-left',
    t1_body: "School teaches addition right-to-left. This is terrible for mental math — you carry uncertain values into a result you haven't formed yet. <strong>Left-to-right means you build the answer progressively</strong>: at every step you hold a real number in your head, not a partial carry.",
    t1_body2: 'This single change will speed up your addition more than any other technique. It takes 1–2 weeks to feel natural; after that, right-to-left will feel wrong.',
